Orange Park, FL 32065

HOA customer care specialist Evergreen Jacksonville, FL
February 2018 to Present
Review and resolve customer complaints 
submit emails and work orders 
inbound and outbound calls 
respond promptly using excel and Microsoft 
follow up calls and responds
Document prosessing

Customer Service Representative Mortgage Specialist's 
2012 to Present
Select Portfolio Servicing
Mortgage Specialist's
Review home owner's income and expenses, and analyze the workout options available to the home owner, based on investor guidelines
- Experience in Loss Mitigation, risk analysis of delinquent loans.

-Analyze liquidation options and financial information for non-performing borrowers and direct resolution as per Company and investor requirements

-Perform Modifications on Mortgage loans to meet a more affordable payment to be able to maintain Home Ownership.

-    Experienced in all Government and home modification documentation

-    Handle all Inbound and outbound calls

-    Work with borrowers, real estate agents, attorneys, agencies, and realtors to determine workout options. Including: loan modifications, pre-foreclosure sales, deeds in lieu, repayment plans, and forbearance agreements

Customer service CITI BANK 
2006 to 2012
Managing a very high call volume through whole day taking over 100 phone calls a day with superior quality on every phone call, also awarded a superstar award for my superb performances.
-    Ensuring that my customer service is to resolve any issues or questions that the clients might have regarding credit.
-    Job includes performing credit line increases credit checks new accounts promotional special offers updating the clients information correctly on a one touch basis with a smile on every call.
-    Final decision making on every adjustment being done to the account weather it's appropriate to me the change
-    Responsible for maintain a scorecard that has set goals to be reached each month as far as quality and schedule adherence and customer service survey's
-    Ensures that any changes or issues that need to be addressed are brought up in meetings so that the company can improve any such changes that might need to be made to assure 100 percent excellent client services.

Customer Service SEARS MCA 
2005 to 2006
Tasks performed at sears included stocking the back room and making sure my area was filled with all required products and sales materials.
-Assuring that every customer was met with great customer service skills and was pleased with each and every questions or concerns that they might have with any products.

Receptionist SHERDIAN HEALTH CARE CENTER 
2005 to 2005
Responsible for managing a switchboard with over 200 lines transferring call to the correct offices of the administrators.
-Liable for all outgoing and incoming faxes are addressed to the correct departments and that all appointments are scheduled with the transportation arrangements for the patients
Assisting all guest that arrive at the center to sign in and make sure all correct information is filled out before preceding into the facility
-Managing all patient care charts with each change or occurrences that has happened based on each individuals needs or strengths or improvements that have been noticed or made.

Activity Assistant IRIS U.S.A. Reception FRONT DESKS 
2003 to 2004
In charge of managing over 400 line switchboard assuring that each call is direct to the correct place of business. And greeting each guest who arrives in main entrance and directing them where needed.
-In charge of picking up mail and delivering to correct individuals mail boxes and checking fax periodically though out day and delivering to correct authorities.
-Scheduling all services that are performed for lunches and meetings in charge of managing food orders and supply orders, along with package delivery upon UPS arrival on a daily basis

High school diploma  ZION BENTON TOWNSHIP HIGHSCHOOL


Microsoft office data entry etc (10+ years), Customer Service
